1
00:00:48,589 --> 00:00:52,036
KING THE LAND

2
00:00:52,449 --> 00:00:54,062
ALL CHARACTERS, LOCATIONS,
ORGANIZATIONS, AND INCIDENTS

3
00:00:54,143 --> 00:00:55,882
DEPICTED IN THIS DRAMA
ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

4
00:00:57,177 --> 00:00:58,595
<i>Are you not going to tell me?</i>

5
00:00:58,679 --> 00:01:01,056
Do you want to see me die of frustration?

6
00:01:04,935 --> 00:01:06,186
It's just…

7
00:01:07,437 --> 00:01:09,481
I have a lot on my mind.

8
00:01:10,774 --> 00:01:12,609
I'm wondering if the work I'm doing now

9
00:01:14,236 --> 00:01:17,572
is what I really wanted to do at a hotel.

10
00:01:21,952 --> 00:01:24,246
This isn't what I dreamed of.

11
00:01:32,045 --> 00:01:33,130
I know.

12
00:01:33,213 --> 00:01:36,675
I should be thankful for my job there
instead of complaining.

13
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:42,514
Goodness.

14
00:01:43,432 --> 00:01:48,061
My baby has finally learned
to grumble and whine.

15
00:01:48,770 --> 00:01:50,647
I always wondered

16
00:01:50,731 --> 00:01:53,817
if I'd be able to see you do this
before I passed away.

17
00:01:59,990 --> 00:02:01,742
What are you saying?

18
00:02:02,326 --> 00:02:03,910
You should be telling me off,

19
00:02:03,994 --> 00:02:06,830
saying that I can't have it all
and to just do my job.

20
00:02:07,539 --> 00:02:10,167
No matter how well-known a restaurant is,

21
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:12,669
it's no use if it's not to your liking.

22
00:02:12,753 --> 00:02:14,171
Who cares about the hotel?

23
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:17,049
You only live once.

24
00:02:17,758 --> 00:02:19,801
You should do what you really want to do.

25
00:02:20,302 --> 00:02:22,554
Don't mind other people,

26
00:02:22,637 --> 00:02:24,222
and don't hesitate either.

27
00:02:24,306 --> 00:02:26,224
Do everything you want to.

28
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:29,019
If it isn't the way,
you can take a detour.

29
00:02:29,102 --> 00:02:31,938
If you fall off a cliff,
you can climb up again.

30
00:02:33,607 --> 00:02:34,691
Okay?

31
00:02:40,113 --> 00:02:41,114
Okay.

32
00:02:41,698 --> 00:02:43,992
Okay, Grandma.

33
00:02:46,828 --> 00:02:48,288
You'll be fine.

34
00:02:48,372 --> 00:02:51,583
I'm here for you,
so do whatever you want to do.

35
00:02:52,876 --> 00:02:54,127
You deserve it.

36
00:02:58,298 --> 00:02:59,341
Okay.

37
00:02:59,925 --> 00:03:01,134
I'll do that.

38
00:03:01,218 --> 00:03:02,302
Good.

39
00:03:16,483 --> 00:03:17,943
I'm done.

40
00:03:19,402 --> 00:03:20,695
I want to leave.

41
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,552
What do you exactly mean…

42
00:03:47,097 --> 00:03:48,473
by leaving?

43
00:03:51,435 --> 00:03:53,186
I want to quit my job at the hotel.

44
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,777
Was there a specific reason

45
00:04:02,112 --> 00:04:03,572
that made you want to quit?

46
00:04:11,746 --> 00:04:15,792
To me, a hotel was a place of happiness.

47
00:04:16,710 --> 00:04:19,254
And that's why I became a concierge.

48
00:04:20,547 --> 00:04:22,883
I wanted to provide the happiest day

49
00:04:22,966 --> 00:04:25,760
to every guest who stayed at the hotel.

50
00:04:26,761 --> 00:04:29,556
But what I'm doing right now
seems far from that.

51
00:04:30,557 --> 00:04:33,059
Although King the Land may be fancy,

52
00:04:33,143 --> 00:04:35,312
and I may make a lot of money
in the Dream Team,

53
00:04:36,438 --> 00:04:38,356
it's not the life I want.

54
00:04:40,025 --> 00:04:41,109
I also…

55
00:04:43,028 --> 00:04:45,322
want to write my own story.

56
00:04:59,794 --> 00:05:01,588
It sounded like a tough decision,

57
00:05:04,216 --> 00:05:05,800
but it was a happy resolution.

58
00:05:08,136 --> 00:05:09,137
That's true.

59
00:05:11,348 --> 00:05:14,518
I want to make a hotel of my own,
no matter how tiny it is.

60
00:05:15,477 --> 00:05:16,937
I want to try it on my own.

61
00:05:24,569 --> 00:05:25,445
One second.

62
00:05:29,491 --> 00:05:30,742
It's me.

63
00:05:30,825 --> 00:05:32,244
Please cancel the event.

64
00:05:32,869 --> 00:05:33,954
Thank you.

65
00:05:36,665 --> 00:05:38,166
What did you just cancel?

66
00:05:40,293 --> 00:05:42,003
It was something important.

67
00:05:46,132 --> 00:05:47,175
But I'll do it later.

68
00:05:53,682 --> 00:05:54,891
I'm sorry.

69
00:05:54,975 --> 00:05:56,184
I must've startled you.

70
00:05:56,685 --> 00:05:57,519
Don't be.

71
00:06:01,231 --> 00:06:02,232
Congratulations.

72
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:05,360
You found what you really wanted to do,

73
00:06:06,194 --> 00:06:07,779
and you're determined to try it.

74
00:06:08,363 --> 00:06:09,823
Congratulations.

75
00:06:09,906 --> 00:06:15,745
Perhaps that was
what I most wanted to hear from you.

76
00:06:17,289 --> 00:06:18,331
Thank you

77
00:06:18,957 --> 00:06:20,292
for sharing

78
00:06:21,584 --> 00:06:23,044
your honest feelings.

79
00:06:26,923 --> 00:06:28,174
But promise me one thing.

80
00:06:29,884 --> 00:06:30,844
What is it?

81
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,346
When you work alone,

82
00:06:35,098 --> 00:06:37,350
you'll face many difficulties.

83
00:06:38,351 --> 00:06:42,355
You'll come across things
that are tough for you to bear alone.

84
00:06:42,439 --> 00:06:44,399
When that happens, don't hesitate…

85
00:06:46,985 --> 00:06:48,153
and call me.

86
00:06:49,529 --> 00:06:50,989
I'll run over right away.

87
00:07:12,802 --> 00:07:15,430
You're the prettiest today
since the day we first met.

88
00:07:15,513 --> 00:07:16,806
You're dazzling.

89
00:07:16,890 --> 00:07:20,101
I was going to blow my nose,
but I can't now that you said that.

90
00:07:20,935 --> 00:07:22,312
Just blow your nose.

91
00:07:22,395 --> 00:07:23,897
Even that looks pretty to me.

92
00:07:26,566 --> 00:07:28,360
So what did you want to say to me?

93
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:31,029
Oh.

94
00:07:37,702 --> 00:07:38,912
No matter where you are,

95
00:07:40,372 --> 00:07:42,040
no matter what you do,

96
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,003
I'll always be on your side.

97
00:07:50,173 --> 00:07:51,841
I wanted to tell you that.

98
00:07:59,432 --> 00:08:00,725
Thank you.

99
00:08:02,435 --> 00:08:03,353
Me too.

100
00:08:05,313 --> 00:08:06,856
I'll always be on your side.

101
00:08:09,484 --> 00:08:10,610
Excuse me.

102
00:08:10,694 --> 00:08:12,195
May I take a photo of you two?

103
00:08:13,113 --> 00:08:14,030
Sure.

104
00:08:16,366 --> 00:08:17,367
You look great.

105
00:08:18,201 --> 00:08:20,245
I'll take the photo now.

106
00:08:20,328 --> 00:08:22,622
One, two, three.

107
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:25,333
Could you take one more?

108
00:08:32,132 --> 00:08:33,550
Okay, one more time.

109
00:08:34,217 --> 00:08:36,970
One, two, three.

110
00:08:41,141 --> 00:08:43,435
FINALE

111
00:09:15,842 --> 00:09:17,802
Thank you for seeing me today.

112
00:09:18,678 --> 00:09:22,015
How could I turn down your offer
to treat me to a meal?

113
00:09:22,724 --> 00:09:25,977
Are you trying to
kill your enemy with kindness?

114
00:09:27,395 --> 00:09:28,855
I wanted to tell you something.

115
00:09:30,565 --> 00:09:33,109
Yes, I'm sure you have lots to say.

116
00:09:34,486 --> 00:09:35,361
I'm listening.

117
00:09:38,406 --> 00:09:39,240
Well…

118
00:09:43,036 --> 00:09:44,370
I would like to quit.

119
00:09:45,205 --> 00:09:46,831
I came to tell you that.

120
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,586
May I ask

121
00:09:52,712 --> 00:09:53,838
the reason?

122
00:09:54,839 --> 00:09:56,007
I want to quit

123
00:09:57,091 --> 00:09:58,927
and date him out in the open.

124
00:09:59,010 --> 00:10:00,970
If I stay here,

125
00:10:01,054 --> 00:10:03,181
I'd have to continue
following your orders.

126
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:07,435
Did you come to declare war?

127
00:10:09,562 --> 00:10:13,107
I came to a realization
after spending time away from him.

128
00:10:13,858 --> 00:10:15,735
I love him so much

129
00:10:15,819 --> 00:10:18,613
that I can't live without him.

130
00:10:23,618 --> 00:10:25,453
You may not be happy with me,

131
00:10:26,162 --> 00:10:28,706
but I know I won't disappoint you.

132
00:10:41,219 --> 00:10:43,346
This is exactly why I like you!

133
00:10:50,436 --> 00:10:51,938
I apologize for my immaturity

134
00:10:52,021 --> 00:10:54,649
and for not separating the personal
from the professional.

135
00:10:54,732 --> 00:10:56,568
When it comes to my children,

136
00:10:56,651 --> 00:10:57,986
I become rather ambitious.

137
00:10:59,070 --> 00:11:01,698
It's all right. I understand.

138
00:11:02,699 --> 00:11:05,785
Thanks to you,
I reached the highest position possible

139
00:11:06,411 --> 00:11:09,205
and found out what I truly wanted.

140
00:11:10,331 --> 00:11:11,416
So thank you.

141
00:11:14,794 --> 00:11:18,131
That's why I'm going to do something
I really want to do.

142
00:11:18,214 --> 00:11:19,048
I see.

143
00:11:19,132 --> 00:11:22,093
I'm sure you'll do a great job,
no matter what it is.

144
00:11:24,095 --> 00:11:25,096
Thank you.

145
00:11:26,431 --> 00:11:29,350
It's my treat today, so please enjoy.

146
00:11:31,019 --> 00:11:32,186
All right.

147
00:11:33,062 --> 00:11:34,188
Thank you.

148
00:11:35,064 --> 00:11:35,982
I'll enjoy it.

149
00:11:42,614 --> 00:11:43,865
So delicious.

150
00:11:58,588 --> 00:12:00,632
Sa-rang, thank you for your hard work.

151
00:12:01,507 --> 00:12:03,760
This is for you. It's from all of us.

152
00:12:06,304 --> 00:12:07,263
Thank you.

153
00:12:08,431 --> 00:12:10,433
I learned so much from everyone.

154
00:12:10,516 --> 00:12:12,894
Don't forget us no matter where you go.

155
00:12:12,977 --> 00:12:14,479
I hope you'll always be happy.

156
00:12:17,523 --> 00:12:19,442
Thank you, everyone.

157
00:12:20,276 --> 00:12:21,486
I'll miss you all.

158
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:27,241
And Ms. Jeon,

159
00:12:28,368 --> 00:12:30,870
you always helped me greatly.

160
00:12:31,788 --> 00:12:33,456
I'll never forget that.

161
00:12:39,253 --> 00:12:40,546
You've done well.

162
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:46,427
I want to hug her too.

163
00:12:46,511 --> 00:12:47,553
Me too.

164
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:51,474
- Sa-rang.
- Don't go.

165
00:12:51,557 --> 00:12:52,725
- Great work.
- Gosh.

166
00:12:52,809 --> 00:12:54,102
You'll stay in touch, right?

167
00:12:54,185 --> 00:12:56,104
- Yes.
- Don't forget us.

168
00:13:19,836 --> 00:13:21,671
"President Gu Won."

169
00:13:28,052 --> 00:13:29,137
Sa-rang.

170
00:13:30,847 --> 00:13:33,099
- Hello.
- It's your last day.

171
00:13:33,683 --> 00:13:34,809
It is.

172
00:13:34,892 --> 00:13:36,436
Mr. Gu went out to work.

173
00:13:36,519 --> 00:13:37,520
It's okay.

174
00:13:38,104 --> 00:13:40,523
Anyway, with our kind Ms. Sa-rang gone,

175
00:13:40,606 --> 00:13:42,275
who will watch over King Hotel?

176
00:13:42,984 --> 00:13:45,528
The talented Mr. No is here,
so why are you worried?

177
00:13:45,611 --> 00:13:46,988
That's true, right?

178
00:13:47,905 --> 00:13:49,365
But with you gone,

179
00:13:49,449 --> 00:13:51,576
my life will be too tiresome.

180
00:13:52,243 --> 00:13:53,828
I must deal with his temper alone.

181
00:13:53,911 --> 00:13:55,371
Don't say that.

182
00:13:55,913 --> 00:13:58,791
He's very considerate of you.
Please take good care of him.

183
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,419
So he said that behind my back?

184
00:14:02,587 --> 00:14:04,547
We should all get together soon
for a drink.

185
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:05,840
Okay, let's meet up.

186
00:14:05,923 --> 00:14:06,883
Sounds good.

187
00:14:09,802 --> 00:14:10,970
Good work.

188
00:14:16,642 --> 00:14:17,977
Thank you.

189
00:14:19,937 --> 00:14:21,105
I'll root for you.

190
00:14:25,234 --> 00:14:26,527
Wait, why are you crying?

191
00:14:27,570 --> 00:14:28,571
I am?

192
00:14:28,654 --> 00:14:29,822
- Come on.
- I'll leave.

193
00:14:29,906 --> 00:14:31,741
- What's with you?
- Are you staying? Bye.

194
00:14:31,824 --> 00:14:33,659
CHEON SA-RANG

195
00:15:04,607 --> 00:15:05,817
CHEON SA-RANG

196
00:16:33,863 --> 00:16:36,157
Wait, how did you find me here?

197
00:16:37,909 --> 00:16:39,202
Congrats on your new chapter.

198
00:16:43,956 --> 00:16:44,999
Thank you.

199
00:16:45,082 --> 00:16:46,167
One second.

200
00:16:53,257 --> 00:16:54,675
They say good shoes

201
00:16:55,593 --> 00:16:57,303
take you to good places.

202
00:17:17,281 --> 00:17:18,366
They're so pretty.

203
00:17:19,867 --> 00:17:20,910
Thank you

204
00:17:22,286 --> 00:17:24,163
for all of your hard work…

205
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,709
at King Hotel.

206
00:17:33,965 --> 00:17:36,509
I get to leave with great memories
thanks to you.

207
00:17:37,385 --> 00:17:38,761
Thank you.

208
00:17:39,428 --> 00:17:40,554
Good work,

209
00:17:41,806 --> 00:17:45,017
our number one best talent.

210
00:17:47,144 --> 00:17:48,312
I was happy here,

211
00:17:49,146 --> 00:17:50,606
President Gu Won.

212
00:17:50,690 --> 00:17:52,149
You're always welcome to visit.

213
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:54,151
We'll have you as our VVIP guest.

214
00:17:54,235 --> 00:17:55,278
It's an honor.

215
00:17:55,361 --> 00:17:57,446
Please make me the VVVVVVIP.

216
00:17:58,072 --> 00:17:58,948
Of course.

217
00:18:00,574 --> 00:18:01,993
- Shall we?
- Okay.

218
00:18:03,953 --> 00:18:05,621
<i>- Can you give me 1,000 won?
- What?</i>

219
00:18:05,705 --> 00:18:08,249
I hear I need to get money
after giving shoes as a gift.

220
00:18:08,332 --> 00:18:09,792
Only then will you not run away.

221
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:12,837
You're right. You knew that?

222
00:18:13,713 --> 00:18:15,256
I can give you 1,000 won.

223
00:18:16,215 --> 00:18:17,258
Wait, my wallet!

224
00:18:17,341 --> 00:18:19,593
- Where is it?
- We left everything at the bus stop.

225
00:18:19,677 --> 00:18:20,594
Sir, stop the car!

226
00:18:42,433 --> 00:18:45,102
These chores never end.

227
00:18:46,311 --> 00:18:48,397
I'll end up developing hand eczema.

228
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:53,610
- Put these on.
- Are you a wolf in sheep's clothing?

229
00:18:54,987 --> 00:18:55,988
Thanks a lot.

230
00:18:56,071 --> 00:18:58,407
I'm about to cry tears of gratitude.

231
00:18:58,490 --> 00:19:01,493
If you have to do it anyway,
try to enjoy it.

232
00:19:01,577 --> 00:19:02,953
But this isn't enjoyable!

233
00:19:03,036 --> 00:19:05,414
I have no pleasure in life,
stuck at home all day!

234
00:19:07,916 --> 00:19:09,460
It's your day off. You're leaving?

235
00:19:10,169 --> 00:19:11,420
I signed up for a workout.

236
00:19:11,503 --> 00:19:14,089
What? Are you out of your mind?

237
00:19:14,673 --> 00:19:17,176
You need to help me out at home
on your day off!

238
00:19:17,259 --> 00:19:19,011
Get a job within the month,

239
00:19:19,094 --> 00:19:20,971
or I'm really done with you.

240
00:19:21,513 --> 00:19:23,682
Do the dishes and clean the bathroom too.

241
00:19:23,765 --> 00:19:26,185
Why am I the only one who has to do this?

242
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:38,238
Don't worry and go, Mom.

243
00:19:38,322 --> 00:19:39,615
I'll keep my eyes on him.

244
00:19:39,698 --> 00:19:41,074
Cho-rong, what's this?

245
00:19:41,158 --> 00:19:42,326
An army drill sergeant.

246
00:19:42,409 --> 00:19:44,119
These guys are the scariest.

247
00:19:45,871 --> 00:19:46,914
You've got ten minutes.

248
00:19:46,997 --> 00:19:48,874
Finish up in ten minutes. Understood?

249
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,835
No, I don't understand.

250
00:19:51,919 --> 00:19:53,795
Then bunny hop until you get it!

251
00:19:53,879 --> 00:19:55,839
Great job, Cho-rong.

252
00:19:56,715 --> 00:19:58,550
Keep an eye on him. I'll be quick.

253
00:19:58,634 --> 00:20:00,260
Okay, be careful of the traffic.

254
00:20:00,344 --> 00:20:01,845
Yes, ma'am!

255
00:20:23,951 --> 00:20:24,826
Thank you.

256
00:20:27,412 --> 00:20:28,247
Please.

257
00:20:34,545 --> 00:20:35,629
What do you think?

258
00:20:35,712 --> 00:20:38,882
It does smell quite different.

259
00:20:38,966 --> 00:20:40,467
It tastes completely different.

260
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,387
We know that too,

261
00:20:44,304 --> 00:20:46,223
but I don't think it's necessary

262
00:20:46,306 --> 00:20:49,560
to place premium coffee machines
used in junior suites and higher

263
00:20:49,643 --> 00:20:51,103
in standard rooms as well.

264
00:20:51,186 --> 00:20:52,437
I agree.

265
00:20:52,521 --> 00:20:55,065
It blurs the service differentiation
between room types.

266
00:20:56,233 --> 00:21:00,153
The standard room
is our most popular unit, right?

267
00:21:01,113 --> 00:21:03,740
- Yes.
- Do you think it's a waste

268
00:21:03,824 --> 00:21:06,535
to provide better coffee and services

269
00:21:06,618 --> 00:21:07,995
to the majority of our guests?

270
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:12,541
They won't notice.
Is this change necessary?

271
00:21:13,166 --> 00:21:15,794
It all tastes the same.

272
00:21:19,298 --> 00:21:22,718
These small changes are what set us apart.

273
00:21:23,427 --> 00:21:25,429
Our hotel has a simple principle.

274
00:21:25,512 --> 00:21:27,556
Regardless of the room they're staying in,

275
00:21:28,307 --> 00:21:31,518
we consider every single guest
at our hotel a VIP.

276
00:21:31,602 --> 00:21:35,188
That is our new principle.

277
00:21:39,109 --> 00:21:40,068
Well then.

278
00:21:41,445 --> 00:21:44,156
Then we'll change the water too.

279
00:21:44,239 --> 00:21:45,198
Thank you.

280
00:21:46,408 --> 00:21:48,660
May we move on to the next item?

281
00:21:48,744 --> 00:21:49,578
Yes.

282
00:21:50,621 --> 00:21:51,663
The next item

283
00:21:52,539 --> 00:21:54,833
is breaking into the European market.

284
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:58,629
According to market research,
tourists have increased,

285
00:21:58,712 --> 00:22:01,798
but the revenues of global hotel chains
continue to drop.

286
00:22:01,882 --> 00:22:05,344
The needs of guests continue to grow
more detailed and diverse.

287
00:22:05,427 --> 00:22:10,015
We won't break into the market
as a large-scale hotel chain.

288
00:22:10,098 --> 00:22:13,769
Focus on purchasing luxury mansions
that can accommodate up to 20 rooms.

289
00:22:13,852 --> 00:22:17,022
A single chain with a thousand styles.

290
00:22:18,106 --> 00:22:21,234
That's our strategy
for the European market.

291
00:22:24,196 --> 00:22:26,406
So this will turn into our staff lounge?

292
00:22:26,490 --> 00:22:28,450
I'm telling you. Why won't you believe me?

293
00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:30,243
We'll really get massage chairs too?

294
00:22:30,327 --> 00:22:31,662
And a nap room too.

295
00:22:31,745 --> 00:22:32,996
No way.

296
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:35,624
Then we can truly relax
when we go on breaks, right?

297
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:37,626
Sure.

298
00:22:39,252 --> 00:22:41,838
It's all thanks to Mr. Gu.

299
00:22:41,922 --> 00:22:43,340
You should be grateful,

300
00:22:43,423 --> 00:22:44,800
work harder when you work,

301
00:22:44,883 --> 00:22:46,510
and rest well on breaks. Okay?

302
00:22:46,593 --> 00:22:47,636
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

303
00:22:49,554 --> 00:22:50,847
Jeez, what are you doing?

304
00:22:50,931 --> 00:22:52,891
- New cologne?
- It's what I always use.

305
00:22:52,974 --> 00:22:55,018
What's this?
Pull your arm out. You're gross.

306
00:22:55,602 --> 00:22:57,646
A new position, a new scent.

307
00:22:57,729 --> 00:22:59,022
How charming.

308
00:22:59,106 --> 00:23:02,359
When will I get promoted
to a position worthy of such a scent?

309
00:23:02,442 --> 00:23:03,402
I really wonder.

310
00:23:16,081 --> 00:23:16,915
We need to talk.

311
00:23:19,042 --> 00:23:20,919
- This is for me?
- Yes.

312
00:23:21,002 --> 00:23:23,171
- It looks bad.
- This is good.

313
00:23:23,964 --> 00:23:26,007
Why are you suddenly so nice to me?

314
00:23:26,091 --> 00:23:27,134
It doesn't suit you.

315
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,392
This actually tastes good.

316
00:23:35,475 --> 00:23:36,852
It's good.

317
00:23:41,648 --> 00:23:42,691
Is that for me?

318
00:23:44,025 --> 00:23:45,193
What could it be?

319
00:23:45,277 --> 00:23:46,403
Should I open it?

320
00:23:51,032 --> 00:23:52,576
Business cards?

321
00:23:52,659 --> 00:23:54,411
I still have lots left.

322
00:23:57,664 --> 00:23:59,332
NO SANG-SIK
STRATEGIC PLANNING DEPARTMENT MANAGER

323
00:24:03,253 --> 00:24:04,337
I'm a department manager?

324
00:24:05,046 --> 00:24:07,424
- You are.
- I'm a department manager!

325
00:24:07,507 --> 00:24:09,176
I'm a department manager!

326
00:24:13,638 --> 00:24:16,057
Are you that happy about it?

327
00:24:16,141 --> 00:24:17,642
Why am I not the head manager?

328
00:24:17,726 --> 00:24:18,602
What?

329
00:24:18,685 --> 00:24:21,146
Ms. Gu said she would make me
the head manager.

330
00:24:21,229 --> 00:24:22,981
I should have switched over then.

331
00:24:23,565 --> 00:24:24,733
I shouldn't have stayed loyal.

332
00:24:24,816 --> 00:24:25,901
There's no reward.

333
00:24:25,984 --> 00:24:27,277
This is such a shame.

334
00:24:28,236 --> 00:24:31,615
I honestly thought
you'd make me the head manager.

335
00:24:31,698 --> 00:24:32,616
You don't like

336
00:24:33,658 --> 00:24:34,826
department manager?

337
00:24:34,910 --> 00:24:36,119
It's not that.

338
00:24:36,203 --> 00:24:38,580
It's just a bummer
that there's no head manager.

339
00:24:38,663 --> 00:24:40,832
It'd be wonderful
to change this to "head."

340
00:24:40,916 --> 00:24:42,209
"Head Manager No Sang-sik."

341
00:24:45,086 --> 00:24:46,421
In that case…

342
00:24:55,055 --> 00:24:56,723
I guess you won't need this either.

343
00:24:57,516 --> 00:24:58,767
What is this?

344
00:24:59,768 --> 00:25:02,062
May I open it? I'm doing it.

345
00:25:04,898 --> 00:25:06,191
You said you didn't need it.

346
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:10,028
It's a watch.

347
00:25:11,613 --> 00:25:13,698
Mr. Gu, your generosity knows no bounds.

348
00:25:14,282 --> 00:25:17,035
Not only are you handsome,
but you're also charming and cool.

349
00:25:17,118 --> 00:25:19,037
That's why you're dating someone.

350
00:25:19,955 --> 00:25:21,164
You didn't want it. Give it back.

351
00:25:21,248 --> 00:25:23,542
No takebacks. You gave it to me.

352
00:25:23,625 --> 00:25:24,543
- Bring it here.
- No.

353
00:25:24,626 --> 00:25:27,003
I will work here until my death.

354
00:25:27,087 --> 00:25:27,921
Thanks a lot.

355
00:25:28,004 --> 00:25:29,673
You didn't want it. Give it back.

356
00:25:29,756 --> 00:25:32,259
Thank you for the promotion!
We go hard! Let's go!

357
00:25:33,635 --> 00:25:34,678
Thanks!

358
00:25:35,512 --> 00:25:36,471
Thank you!

359
00:25:39,474 --> 00:25:41,226
It is I, Department Manager No!

360
00:25:56,866 --> 00:25:58,368
